For each candidate root `x` of the input array `A`, consider `x = y * z` where `y` and `z` are candidates for the left/right subtrees of `x`, ie. we use the rule-of-product to accumulate the count `cnt` of subtrees, initially set to 1 for `x` as a tree comprised of a single root node.

