for num `i`, if `m * n == i`, number of trees for `i` is `1 + count(m) * count(n)`, means root `i` self, add number of trees when `m` is root times number of trees when `n` is root.
```
    public int numFactoredBinaryTrees(int[] A) {
        if(A==null || A.length==0)
            return 0;
        Map<Integer,Long> map = new HashMap<>();
        Arrays.sort(A);
        for(int i=0; i<A.length; i++){
            long count = 1;
            for(int j=0; j<i; j++){
                if(A[i]%A[j]==0 && map.containsKey(A[i]/A[j])){
                    count += map.get(A[i]/A[j]) * map.get(A[j]);
                }
            }
            map.put(A[i],count);
        }
        long sum = 0;
        for(long cnt : map.values())
            sum += cnt;
        return (int) (sum % (Math.pow(10,9) + 7));
    }
```

