The idea is very simple. We can define subproblem dp[i] as the number of different trees rooted A[i]. 
Here is the recurision formula: dp[i] = sum(dp[x] * dp[y] | x * y = i). To reduce the complexity we can only compute where x <= y, and plus x > y on the time x < y. 
