solutions.content:
Main Points :
Sort the array , as we have to find for each element present in arr[i] , **can we make it a parent node by multplying its children** , basically does **both factors of a element are present in order to make it a parent node.**
If we find that the factors are indeed present **we further have to multiply the number of ways of both children** ,in which these children can be formed if they are present as parent node.
so for each element we store the number of ways in which it can be a parent element in a dp array.
```
class Solution {
    public int numFactoredBinaryTrees(int[] arr) {

        int n = arr.length;
        Arrays.sort(arr);

        long trees = 0;
        long mod = (long)1e9+7;
		// making a dp array to store at each point the numbers of ways to make a tree if the current element is taken as parent node
        long []dp = new long[n];

        for( int i=0; i<n; i++ ){
			// current trees initialized as 1 , as a number can always make a single by itself
            long curr = 1;

            int lo = 0;
            int hi = i-1;

			// two pointers approach to find the factors of current element and if both factors are present in the array
            while( lo <= hi ){

                long prod = arr[lo] * arr[hi];
				// check to find factors and second check to make sure that the number is valid ( i did this check as i was encountering a problem in a testcase even though the numbers were big their product was small and coming out to be exact as current element)
                if( prod == ( arr[i] % mod ) && arr[lo] <= ( arr[i]/2 ) && arr[hi] <= ( arr[i]/2 ) ){
                    int diff = 2;
					// if both the numbers are same there is only one way we can arrange as either being on left or right is same for them
                    if( arr[lo] == arr[hi] ) diff = 1;
                    curr = ( curr +  ( ( ( dp[hi] * dp[lo] ) % mod ) * diff ) % mod ) % mod;
                    lo++;
                    hi--;
                }
                else if ( prod > arr[i] ) hi--;
                else lo++;
            }
            // storing the current trees
            dp[i] = curr;
			// storing total trees we can make
            trees = ( trees + curr )%mod;
        }

        return (int)trees;
    }
}
```

