**Read the below steps to understand the logic**

***Upvote if you like it!!***

**Steps**
1. Sort the given arr. ```sort(arr.begin(),arr.end());```
2. Declare map and set all element value by 1 ex: ```mp[auto num: arr]=1;```
3. Declare loop which will start from first index untill last index. ```for(int i=1;i<n;i++)```
		* Declare nested loop inside previous loop which will start from 0'th untill i'th index for each i'th element.```for(int j=1;j<i;j++)``` and declare count as 0.
		* Check whether arr[j] is factor of arr[i] of not, if yes then check divident value is present inside map or not, if yes than increment count by  multiply of arr[j] and divident second map value.
		* after that increment map's second value of arr[i] by count.
4.  return sum of second map's values of each element of given array after taking modules. 

```
public:
    int numFactoredBinaryTrees(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n=arr.size();
        sort(arr.begin(),arr.end());
        map<int,long long> mp;
        for(auto num: arr)
            mp[num]=1;

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            long long count=0;
            auto it=mp.find(arr[i]);
            for(int j=0;j<i;j++){
                if(arr[i]%arr[j]==0){
                    auto it1 = mp.find(arr[i]/arr[j]);
                    auto it2=mp.find(arr[j]);
                    if(it1!=mp.end()){
                        count+=(it1->second)*(it2->second);
                    }
                }
            }
            it->second+=count;
        }
        long long  sum=0;
        for(auto it4=mp.begin();it4!=mp.end(); it4++){
            sum+= it4->second;
        }
        return sum%(1000000007);
    }
```

