Kadane Algo - Complexity O(size of array) But maxm size array we can make is of order 10^7
So according to constraints, we cannot duplicate the array k times and apply Kadane
Say arr = [1,-2,1], k = 5 
Approach-
1. Duplicate the given array. 
-- So duplicated array will be [1 -2 1 1 -2 1]

2. Apply Kadane on the duplicated array. Here it will give maxm subarray sum as 2(1 from first half+ 1 from sec half)
--The maximum subarray sum can be constituted with elements from two possible ways
---Way 1:From first two duplicates [1 -2 1][1 -2 1]..(k-2) duplicates
---Way 2: From all the duplicates. [1 -2 1]...(k-2) duplicates..[1 -2 -1]

3. Find sum of all elements of given array. Here sum = 1-2+1=0
4. if sum>0 then result= Result of step 2 + (k-2) * sum          (Way 2 of step 2)
-- else result=sum                                                                   (Way 1 of step 2)
---So here result=2                            

