We need the solve a function:**F(A, K)**
what is its realtion with **F(A, K-1)**?
a simple observation is that F(A, K) >= F(A, K-1).
So when will F(A, K) > F(A, K-1)?
**key observation here**: THe necessary condition（NOTE:not sufficient) is that all total K arrays must be utilized to make it greater than F(A, K-1).

