There are three cases:
1. if k==1, which is the same as find the maximum subarray;
2. if k>1: 
	1. if the sum of the array is less than or equal to 0, we can each find max subarray in the first array or concatenation of two arraies, for example
 		1. [1,2,-4]+[1,2,-4] the subarray max is 1+2 = 3, which is in the first array; 
		2. [1,-4,1]+[1,-4,1] the subarray max is 1+1 = 2, which is in the first two array;
	2. if the sum of the array is greater than 0, we have to add the(k-1)*sum(array) and maximum subarray of array,
				1.prefix+[maximum subarry] + suffix +(k-2)*sum(array)+ prefix+[maximum subarry] + suffix =(prefix+[maximum subarry] + suffix + prefix+[maximum subarry] + suffix) +(k-2)*sum(array), so we only need to consider the first part, the maximum subarray sum of the first part is [maximum subarry] + suffix + prefix+[maximum subarry] = sum(array)+maximum subarray, since the sum of the array is greater than 0, so it must be the sum(array)+subarrrysum. hope it helpes.
