solutions.content:
# Intuition
It looks like a subarray max sum problem.

# Approach
If the sum of all elements in arr > 0 we will have to add up all sums of arr by repeating it k-2 times. -2 is because we are going to exclude the most left and the most right arrays where we can maximize the sums by finding the maximum sums of the subarray which have starting point from the 0 index (this is the last array in the sequence) and the subarray with the ending point at the latest index (this is the first array in the sequence).
The edge cases:
1) When k == 1 we need to find a subarray max sum. 
2) When the sum of all elements in arr is less or equal to 0, then either we need to find a subarray max sum or the sum of the maximum sums of the subarray which have starting point from the 0 index and the subarray with the ending point at the latest index. This is because those subarrays will concatanate sitting next to each other. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    func kConcatenationMaxSum(_ arr: [Int], _ k: Int) -> Int {
        if k == 1 {
            return max(maxSubarraySum(arr), 0)
        }

        let sum = arr.reduce(0, +)

        let count = arr.count
        var leftSum = sum
        var rightSum = sum
        var maxRightSum = sum
        var maxLeftSum = sum
        for i in 0..<count-1 {
            leftSum -= arr[count-1-i]
            maxLeftSum = max(maxLeftSum, leftSum)
            rightSum -= arr[i]
            maxRightSum = max(maxRightSum, rightSum)
        }

        if sum <= 0 {
            return max(maxLeftSum + maxRightSum, maxSubarraySum(arr), 0)
        }

        let produce: Int64 = (Int64(sum) * Int64(k-2) + Int64(maxLeftSum) + Int64(maxRightSum)) % 1000000007
        return Int(produce)
    }

    private func maxSubarraySum(_ arr: [Int]) -> Int {
        var sum = 0
        var maxResult = Int.min
        for num in arr {
            sum += num
            if sum > maxResult {
                maxResult = sum
            }
            if sum < 0 {
                sum = 0
            }
        }
        return maxResult
    }
}
```

