# Approach
Use Kadane's Algorithm to find ans(MaximumSubarraySum).
There can be 2 cases when K==1 and K>1.
return 0 , when all elements are negative.
return ans, when totalsum is negative but ans is positive and k>1
return ttsum*max(0,k-2)+ans, when ttsum is positive and ans is also positive.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n*min(0,k-2));

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int kConcatenationMaxSum(vector<int>& arr, int k) {
        ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false);
        cin.tie(0);
        cout.tie(0);
        int n = arr.size();
    int ans = 0;
    int sum =0;
    long long ttsum =0;
    for(int i =0;i<n*min(2,k);i++)
    {
         if(i<n)ttsum+=arr[i];
        sum+=arr[i%n];
        if(sum<arr[i%n])
        {
            sum = arr[i%n];
        }
        ans = max(ans,sum);

    }
    arr.clear();
    return (max(0ll,max((long long)ans,ttsum* max(0,k-2)+ans)))%1000000007;

    }
};
```

