# Intuition
Use Kadane's Algorithm To Find MAX_SUM_SUBARRAY
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
Just Handle 3 cases:
Case 1: when k == 1, Just Return Kadane's Algorithm i.e kadaneOfFirstArr

Case 2: when k > 1 & SUM_OF_ARR < 0 , Return Kadane's of first two arr
i.e kadaneOfTwoArr

Case 3: when k > 1 & SUM_OF_ARR > 0 , Return Kadane's of first two arr + (k-2)*sum

Just Dry Run for all above cases, you will understand lot better
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    int mod=1000000007;

    public int kConcatenationMaxSum(int[] arr, int k) {
        if(k==1){
            return kadaneOfFirstArr(arr);
        }else{
            long sum=0;
            for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
                sum+=arr[i];
            }

            if(sum<0){
                int val= kadaneOfTwoArr(arr);

                if(val<0){
                    return 0;
                }else{
                    return val;
                }
            }else{
                int val=kadaneOfTwoArr(arr);
                return (int)(val+((k-2)*sum)%mod)%mod;
            }
        }
    }

    public int kadaneOfFirstArr(int []arr){
       long MAX_END_HERE=arr[0];
        long MAX_SO_FAR=arr[0];



        for(int i=1;i<arr.length;i++){
            MAX_END_HERE+=arr[i]%mod;
            MAX_END_HERE=Math.max(MAX_END_HERE,arr[i]);
            MAX_SO_FAR=Math.max(MAX_SO_FAR,MAX_END_HERE);
        }
        if(MAX_SO_FAR < 0)
        {
            MAX_SO_FAR = 0;
        }
        return (int)MAX_SO_FAR;
    }

    public int kadaneOfTwoArr(int []arr){
        int n=arr.length;
        int []newArr=new int[n+n];


        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            newArr[i]=arr[i];
        }

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            newArr[n+i]=arr[i];
        }

        long MAX_END_HERE=newArr[0];
        long MAX_SO_FAR=newArr[0];

        for(int i=1;i<newArr.length;i++){
            MAX_END_HERE+=newArr[i]%mod;
            MAX_END_HERE=Math.max(MAX_END_HERE,newArr[i]);
            MAX_SO_FAR=Math.max(MAX_SO_FAR,MAX_END_HERE);
        }

        return (int)MAX_SO_FAR;


        // return kadaneOfFirstArr(nums);
    }
}
